body_html: The underlying error seems to indicate that the "TreePredictions" op isn't registered when the graphdef is being imported before the graph is frozen. This is surprising, since it's clearly being used successfully earlier in the script, so I'm wondering if it's a bug with how the op_dict in Python is populated, maybe related to the fact that the Random Forest ops are in contrib?

body: The underlying error seems to indicate that the "TreePredictions" op isn't registered when the graphdef is being imported before the graph is frozen. This is surprising, since it's clearly being used successfully earlier in the script, so I'm wondering if it's a bug with how the op_dict in Python is populated, maybe related to the fact that the Random Forest ops are in contrib?
